other_tests.procedure_name: Biopsy of the left cervical lymph node
other_tests.findings: Features of a reactive process, with no diagnostic features of a malignant or lymphoproliferative disorder.

other_tests.procedure_name: Biopsy of the left axillary lymph node
other_tests.findings: Breast carcinoma, negative for estrogen and progesterone receptors, positive for HER2, with extranodal extension and extensive lymphovascular invasion.
Serum cortisol level rose from a baseline of 2.5 μg per deciliter to 13.0 μg per deciliter at 30 minutes and to 18.2 μg per deciliter at 60 minutes.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Indicates that the adrenal glands are capable of responding normally to corticotropin.

other_tests.findings: Symmetric gadolinium-enhancing mass (1.0 cm by 1.0 cm by 1.1 cm) at the base of the third ventricle, surrounding the infundibular recess.
